node.text:
I recently started following this bomb.com self help coach on my personal Instagram account. @therealjoirizarry 

Her daily convos/advice/ viewpoints are spot on in this stage of growth and healing. 

This particular post resonates with me as I started setting hella boundaries. Now I can identify that empty feeling, the loss that she speaks of. Maybe you can relate?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head in Austin, Texas with @tanner_hamilton22, @atxlien, and @therealjoirizarry. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text:
This is what depression and anxiety looks like. This picture was taken one week before my son Kenneth Thomas Gaskin, Jr. 1984-2009 RIP died by suicide, 11 years ago. He is the inspiration for @asafeplaceinsideyourhead 
.
.
.
Mental health awareness and suicide prevention shouldn’t need a special day, it’s what we should work on every day.  If you know someone who seems struggling or if you’re struggling, reach out and say “R U Okay?” Or say to someone, “I’m not ok “. 
.
.
If you want to join a closed Facebook group designed for open discussions on mental health issues join A Safe Place Inside your Head and we’re here for you! - @therealjoirizarry  @tanner_hamilton22  @atxlien 

#worldsuicidepreventionday #suicideprevention #suicideawarness #stopsuicide #endthestigma #areyouokay #areyouok #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealthadvocate #safeplaceinsideyourhead

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by A Safe Place Inside Your Head on September 09, 2021 tagging @tanner_hamilton22. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Aya @AyaReina Friendly reminder that suicide prevention isn't just saying "here if you need to talk!" and posting a hotline number. it's healthcare. it's housing. it's adequate social welfare. it's food security. it's actually being able to access mental health services quickly. 1:20 1:20AM-9/9/21-TwitterWebApp AM 9/9/21 Twitter Web'.

node.text:
During #suicideawarenessmonth this is most important. Advocating for the right for everyone to have the ability to get mental health support quickly regardless of financial status. Having better options for both providers and patients because I’m a firm believer that if we pay therapist and psychiatrist their worth WHILE providing low cost or free mental healthcare we all win. We save lives, we don’t leave anyone behind and most importantly we help people live their most authentic lives. This is a collective effort we must have from society because I look at all my fellow people and see so many suffering that can’t get help. Me and my mom created this account/ nonprofit to change the narrative on mental health and to normalize conversations about very difficult topics and we are just getting started. We hope you have enjoyed the journey and stick around for the change we want to see in the world. - @tanner_hamilton22 
.
.
.
.
.
📸= AyaReina on Twitter
.
.
.
#suicideawarenessmonth #asafeplaceinsideyourhead #howcanwehelp #youareamazing #keepgoing #pleasekeepfighting #suicideprevention #suicideawarness #depression #anxiety

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head on September 09, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Tweet Viral Tweets Pain Depression & Anxiety @ILLUMINUSNUMB "ur so polite" thank i was raised in constant fear of upsetting people 9:26 PM 9/8/21 Twitter for iPhone 12.1K Retweets 492 Quote Tweets 49K Likes'.

node.text:
This 100%, I am so scared of upsetting people that it’s made me a perfectionist with anxiety. I always feel like I’m forgetting something to the point I start overthinking and overanalyzing situations and in which I end up hurting my own feelings. Anyone else feel this way lol? - @tanner_hamilton22 
.
.
.
.
.
📸= @illuminusnumb
.
.
.
.
.
#anxiety #fearoffailure #perfectionist #anxietyrelief #anxietyattack #anxiousattachment #idontwanttoupsetanyone #suicideawarenessmonth #keepgoing #youareamazing #depression

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by A Safe Place Inside Your Head on September 09, 2021 tagging @jaronmyers, and @tanner_hamilton22. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Viral Tweets Jaron Myers @jaronmyers We're all so emotionally damaged from this last year and a half that Steve from Blue's Clues was like" have to address the nation" 11:47AM AM 9/8/21 Twitter for iPhone 25.2K Retweets 608 Quote Tweets 149K Likes'.

node.text:
This made me laugh so hard, I swear I needed that closure from Steve and I’m glad I got it. Maybe he can close the time rift if what’s been a crazy year….emotionally I’ve grown because I’ve had too. Navigating the waters of these last 2-3 years has been hard for everyone but I’m proud of you for continuing to keep going. Have a beautiful day. - @tanner_hamilton22 
.
.
📸 = @jaronmyers
.
.
.
#bluesclues #stevefrombluesclues #anxiety #depression #howcanwehelp #asafeplaceinsideyourhead #keepgoing #wewillbeokay #suicideawarenessmonth #depression #depressionhelp #dearevanhansenmemes

May be an image of text that says 'hattie gladwell @hatttiegladwell Just because a person is okay today doesn't mean they'll be okay tomorrow. Mental illness can strike at any time. So please don't say 'well you were fine yesterday', because mental illness doesn't care about timing. And a person smiling doesn't mean they're suffering any less.'.

node.text:
We don’t pick the days we have to fight the battle. Like, “oh today’s Tuesday, I won’t be mentally unstable.”

We don’t pick that moment that the memory or trigger hits us and we unravel. 

Mental illness doesn’t follow a timeline and so many of us have learned to smile or act “normal” during an episode.  The roadmap for a mental health issue looks different for everyone. 

We need grace, and understanding, and sometimes just a little space. - @therealjoirizarry 

📸 @hattiegladwell on Twitter 
.
.
.
.
.
#bipolarawareness #depressionawareness #mentalhealthawareness #dissociation #overthinking #racingthoughts😣 #mentalillnessrecovery #mentalhealthmemes🖤 #asafeplaceinsideyourhead

node.text:
Why is that we vividly remember every cringe worthy memory that we have made in our lifetime?

And why do we remember them every time we try to go to sleep at night? 

Why can I barely remember something good that happened just yesterday? 

Just, why? - @therealjoirizarry 
.
.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head in Austin, Texas. May be an image of text that says 'mom @thewildwatsons If a friend hasn't responded to my text but see them active on social media, it's probably because they are overtired overworked and taking a well-deserved break to scroll. You're not entitled to someone's down time. True friends understand that you can't pour from an empty cup'.

node.text:
That’s me, I’m the friend. 

I’m not gonna lie. When I need a break from reality, I turn to media and leave out the social part. Sometimes I wanna be alone and just meme hunt and laugh or find content that helps me get my head back on straight. It doesn’t mean I want to comment or engage, i just wanna be somewhere in the background. 

So give your friends like me one small break. Give them time and space to unwind. 

Now back to meme hunting …… 😆 @therealjoirizarry 

📸 @thewildwatsons on Twitter 
.
.
.
.
